29/12/2002
EDIRNE, Turkey -- Police seized a large shipment of heroin Saturday (28 December) at the border checkpoint in Edirne. According to their preliminary reports, the shipment amounted to some 23 kg of heroin. Five people are in custody, reportedly including the brother-in-law of Turkish entrepreneur Hayyam Garipoglu. Police suspect the shipment was bound for Western Europe. (Anadolu Agency - 29/12/02; TRT - 28/12/02)
